    <p>On 1995, Aling Nena, the former owner of Aling Nena Sari Sari Store (the picture in the middle), decided to venture on a small business, now called Aling Nena Sari-Sari Store. The reason why she ventured on this business is that she had to find a new source of income to support a family of 10. In her Sari-Sari store, she started selling some detergents, soaps and some drinks. Unfortunately, after 5 years, Aling Nena suffered a disease called MERS CORONA VIRUS. In effect, the oldest son of Aling Nena (the picture on the left) took over the business and his name is Fen Nena. <br> <img src="detergent.jpg" height ="15%" width="15%"><img src="soap.gif" height ="15%" width="15%"><img src="coke.jpeg" height ="15%" width="15%"><img src="c2.jpeg"><center><h4> Available Products Here in Aling Nena's Sari Sari Store</h4></center></p>
